text: Throughout the years of being hated by "True Resident Evil fans" this video game film series still remains the best video game film series of all time grossing over a billion dollars, something you can't say about Mortal Kombat, Silent Hill, Tomb Raider, Doom or Street Fighter. Be proud Resi fans, that the Resident Evil movie (which you despise) has accumulated over a billion dollars throughout the years. Which is a huge achievement. Why? Hollywood hates video game adaptations. But after seeing the Resident Evil movies last nearly 15 years and continue to gross more and more money each release- I am most certain- that this is the final chapter of Resident Evil but a new beginning for future video game movies like Halo, Mass Effect, Call Of Duty, Metal Gear Solid, Legend Of Zelda, etc. and not CGI films but Hollywood A list films. You can hate Resident Evil, Milla, and Paul all you want but you can't deny that their efforts weren't successful- just wait- in time you will understand what I am saying. Resident Evil will be the pioneer of video game movie adaptations.

I think there is potential for a few quality films if everything is centered on the Arklay/Mansion incident and the fall of Raccoon City.  The existing Resident Evil series is so far removed from real Resident Evil, I always thought the real Resident Evil could make a better movie if the effort went towards it.

text: I try my best to like the RE films but the potential of this franchise has simply been squandered.  So many great characters rarely given any screen time or lazy dialogue or even written out of the story completely. I had high hopes for this franchise until about Resident evil Extinction...After that film i lost all hope.  Example where did the little girl angela ashford go after the 2nd film? Why was a major character like barry burton given such a small part and then killed off in the most recent installment of the franchise? Where is rebecca chambers?!?!?! Why has chris redfield only appeared in a single film? Why has leon kennedy only appeared in a single film? These are not small throw away characters they deserved better than they have got so far in the franchise.  Why has a film not been set in caliban cove? Why was the mansion proper used so little in the first film? It played a major part in the book and game. Where is sherry birkin from resident evil 2(The game) Chief irons from re2 Brad vickers Annette birkin...........I mean dang the list is endless of how they could have added so much more to the lore and world of the films and yet choose to put stereotypes and 2nd rate characters in place of fan favorites.

text: TO ALL THE HATERS:  You'll bash this for being a series that "needs to die", but I GUARANTEE you're eager as Hell to see the 35th movie about Batman, or the 12th Fast & Furious, or the latest soft reboot of a remaked rebooted remake.  "Fans of the games hate these movies". Speak for yourself, NOT for the public.  "These movies are stupid, they're all just big, dumb action with no cohesive plot". ... SO? Not every movie is "Citizen Kane". What's wrong with a big, dumb, action-packed popcorn flick?  Milla and Paul actually have FUN making these, and it fucking SHOWS. I'll take a fun, "dumb", nonsensical movie that I can sit back and enjoy over some bloated summer blockbuster that's only being made to sell toys.  Don't like the movies? Fine. Move along, and watch something else. Meanwhile, THIS die-hard RE fan is going to see this flick opening weekend.

text: To all the critics, please view this as nothing but a mindless action flick, as all the RE movies have ever been. Any plot is just kind of thrown together and used as background noise to give the characters some direction. It is just like the RE games. They were fun games (at least the older ones), and that has everything to do with the mechanics used to play them, and cool cut scenes interspersed throughout. The story never made sense as that was never their intention. When you view it for what it is, it actually looks like a fun movie.  Final thought, compare it to the Die Hard or Transporter movies. They don't make much sense. It's all about mindless action and that's how it must be viewed to enjoy it.

text: Strange thought: The RE movies are the only movies to retain a pre-9/11 sensibility: silly, overblown, and dependent on ridiculous CGI that went out of fashion by 2004 (consider that the 1st movie came out in 2000). On top of that, meandering and directionless, jumping from one installment to the other with no commitment of story. It's the kind of movie nobody would make today now that long-form storytelling and dense world-building is standard requirement of franchise films and audience satisfaction.  So on one hand I like the RE movies for this reason...on the other, I'm glad they're ending now: I was done with the series by #2.

text: I consider myself to be a huge RE game fan. I own 3 different versions of 1,2 and 3. As well as multiple copies of every re related game that followed. I speed run nemesis 3 times a week. I do not go a month without playing through 0,1,2 and 3. Its just something that i enjoy doing on a regular basis when i have down time. I am sick and tired of so called RE purists online thinking they can come on here and speak for all of us.  I for one enjoy the hell out of these movies. To be honest, the story line in the game while insane and outlandish, is the weakest part of the series and is not the defining factor of the series for me. I simply love the world and characters. I really really like that they did their own thing with the movies. When i want traditional RE i will go play the first 3 games. The rest of you negative nancies really need to learn to give things a chance, rather than having unreal expectations for everything. This isn't the first and it wont be the last time that your beloved random series deviates from the source material when a movie is being made. That does not mean bad, it just means that you all are too smug to accept change.

People are just biased towards any movie that they haven't taken the time to watch or just aren't into. This series wasn't just slapped together, the directors and writers made an effort because they're passionate about the films. text: Looks like a lot of fun.  Count me in!  I know it's popular to hate on the RE movies because they changed so much from the games (which I totally understand and respect and I hope we do get a reboot in the future that sticks properly to the games)...    ...but sue me, they're great entertainment and a good example of "dumb fun" done right!  They're the sort-of movies that are perfect for popping in on a rainy-day or marathoning with friends and some beer.  They're stupid and schlocky in all the right ways to make them a fun and breezy watch, and there's just enough of a vague ongoing story to keep you invested.  And if the trailer is any indication, this looks to be a good conclusion.  The visuals look really slick and stylish, they're book-ending the series with the original which will help usher in a sense of finality, and it seems to have an end-game in play.  So yeah, I'll totally be there opening day.
